<element xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xmlns:zenta="http://magwas.rulez.org/zenta"
         xsi:type="zenta:BasicObject"
         name="Controller annotations and naming"
         id="adc7c595-d583-4ec1-b75b-6a5bb378da81"
         ancestor="behaviour">
   <documentation>In java

* the class must have a @RestController annotation
* the interface methods must be annotated with @GetMapping or @PostMapping annotations according to the HTTP method and url path associated with the controller
* the interface parameters should be annotated with @RequestBody annotation if that is mandated by the design and the request type is not x-www-form-urlencoded
* the parameters according to path parameters should be annotated with @PathParam
</documentation>
</element>
